ction of the central articles published on the debate over the past decade. The essays encompass a wide range ofaspects: the difference between virtue ethics and traditional duty ethics; present arguments for and against virtue ethics; the practical implications of virtue ethics and the Aristotelian and Kantian attitudes to virtue ethics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEthics. 0aVirtue. 0aVirtues. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aAlderman, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHursthouse, Rosalind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLouden, Robert B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontague, Phillip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSantas, Gerasimos X., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlote, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, Robert C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStatman, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStocker, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwanton, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelazco, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelazco, Trianosky, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatson, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archi